text.tspan: O teach me what it meaneth
O teach me what it meaneth:
Teach me that if none other
Yet still, Thy blood, O Jesus,
O teach me what it meaneth,
Yea, teach me, till there gloweth
In this cold heart of mine
Of that pure love of Thine.
O teach me what it meaneth,
For I am full of sin;
And grace alone can reach me,
O teach me, for I need Thee,
The chief of all the sinners
O teach me what it meaneth:
The rest which Thou dost give
Who look to Thee and live.
* The Compilers prefer that the following three lines be used in place of the last three lines in verse 2: Had sinned but only I, / Yet still, O blessed Savior, / Thou on the cross must die.
